{
 "name": "RPlog_Etiquette_101",
 "title": "Etiquette 101",
 "summary": "On the O'paal Spaceport Plaza, the scarred, half-cybernetic killer Morganna arrives for a covert training session run by her handler, the genteel 'man in red' codenamed Atrox, who poses as a refined gentleman while evaluators secretly observe. Atrox drills the feral, foul-mannered Morganna in etiquette, beginning with a punishing control bracelet that mimics her abusive father's voice and shocks her into compliance, then teaches her to walk on a gentleman's arm and ride a cab with poise. The lesson escalates into a role-play test against the cat-faced agent Gabriel, who plays the haughty foreign dignitary 'Bourne', forcing Morganna to suppress her rage and attempt diplomatic courtesy despite repeated failures and slips into menace. Atrox and Gabriel coach her through proper greetings, pronunciation, and composure, slowly drawing out a more controlled, almost likeable demeanor beneath the violence. The session ends with Atrox dismissing the convoy and a waiter discreetly passing Morganna an encrypted holochip; she reads a praising message signed 'LA', a small smile creeping across her lips at her own progress.",
